@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}



<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="~/css/privacy.css">
    <title>Privacy Policy for Student Planner</title>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Privacy Policy for Student Planner</h1>
        <p>Last Updated: 2023-09-18</p>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

        <section>
            <h3>1.1. Personal Information</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Name: We collect your name to personalize your user experience within the App.</li>
                <li>Email Address: Your email address is collected to facilitate communication and send account-related notifications.</li>
                <li>User Profile: You may choose to provide additional information such as a profile picture or bio to enhance your profile within the App.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h3>1.2. Usage Information</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>App Usage Data: We collect data about how you interact with the App, such as the pages you visit, features you use, and the duration of your sessions.</li>
                <li>Device Information: We may gather device-specific information, including your device type, operating system, and browser type.</li>
                <li>Log Data: When you use the App, we automatically collect log data, including your IP address, access times, and actions taken within the App.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h3>1.3. Content Information</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Events and Schedules: You can input information about educational events, lectures, and schedules, including their time slots, locations, and descriptions.</li>
                <li>Uploaded Files: You have the option to upload files to specific events or lectures within the App, enhancing your educational planning experience.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Communication: We may use your email address to send you important account-related notifications and updates.</li>
            <li>App Improvement and Analysis: We analyze user data to enhance the App's functionality, user experience, and content.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>3. How We Share Your Information</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Collaboration: Information you post or edit for events or lectures may be shared with others in your groups for collaboration purposes within the App.</li>
            <li>Service Providers: We may share your information with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating the App.</li>
            <li>Legal Requirements: We may disclose your information in response to legal requests, court orders, or when required by law.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>


        <section>
            <h2>4. Your Choices and Rights</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Account Settings: You can review and edit your account information through the App's settings.</li>
                <li>Email Communications: You can opt out of receiving non-essential email communications from us.</li>
                <li>Data Access and Deletion: You have the right to request access to your personal information or request its deletion, subject to legal requirements.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
</body>
</html>
